cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with volumetric image segmentation using convolutional neural networks. The paper also proposes a novel approach to learning shape representations using point clouds, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of neural networks also suggests the possibility of the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on anatomical shape representation could also place it under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
